ID,Level,Principle,Success Criterion,Checklist Question,Pass/Fail,Notes
1.1.1,A,Perceivable,Non-text Content,"Do all images, icons, and controls have meaningful alt text or labels?",,
1.2.1,A,Perceivable,Audio-only & Video-only (Prerecorded),Is alternative text/transcript available for audio-only and video-only media?,,
1.2.2,A,Perceivable,Captions (Prerecorded),Are captions provided for prerecorded videos with audio?,,
1.2.3,A,Perceivable,Audio Description or Media Alternative,Is audio description or transcript provided for video-only?,,
1.2.4,AA,Perceivable,Captions (Live),Are captions available for live multimedia?,,
1.2.5,AA,Perceivable,Audio Description (Prerecorded),Do prerecorded videos have audio descriptions?,,
1.3.1,A,Perceivable,Info & Relationships,"Is content structured with headings, lists, tables, and labels correctly?",,
1.3.2,A,Perceivable,Meaningful Sequence,Is reading/navigation order logical?,,
1.3.3,A,Perceivable,Sensory Characteristics,Is information not conveyed by color/shape alone?,,
1.3.4,AA,Perceivable,Orientation,Can the site work in both portrait and landscape?,,
1.3.5,AA,Perceivable,Identify Input Purpose,"Are input fields programmatically identifiable (e.g., autofill, ARIA)?",,
1.4.1,A,Perceivable,Use of Color,"Is color not the only means of conveying info (e.g., error states)?",,
1.4.2,A,Perceivable,Audio Control,Can users pause/stop/adjust auto-playing audio?,,
1.4.3,AA,Perceivable,Contrast (Minimum),Is text contrast at least 4.5:1 (normal) or 3:1 (large)?,,
1.4.4,AA,Perceivable,Resize Text,Can text be resized up to 200% without loss of content?,,
1.4.5,AA,Perceivable,Images of Text,Are text images avoided (except essential cases)?,,
1.4.10,AA,Perceivable,Reflow,Does content reflow without horizontal scrolling up to 400% zoom?,,
1.4.11,AA,Perceivable,Non-text Contrast,"Do icons, controls, and graphics have a 3:1 contrast ratio?",,
1.4.12,AA,Perceivable,Text Spacing,Can users adjust text spacing without losing content/functionality?,,
1.4.13,AA,Perceivable,Content on Hover/Focus,"Is hover/focus content dismissible, hoverable, and persistent?",,
2.1.1,A,Operable,Keyboard,Is all functionality available via keyboard?,,
2.1.2,A,Operable,No Keyboard Trap,Can users navigate without getting trapped in elements?,,
2.1.4,A,Operable,Character Key Shortcuts,Are single-key shortcuts adjustable or disabled?,,
2.2.1,A,Operable,Timing Adjustable,Can users extend/disable time limits?,,
2.2.2,A,Operable,"Pause, Stop, Hide","Can users pause/stop/mute moving, blinking, or auto-updating content?",,
2.3.1,A,Operable,Three Flashes or Below Threshold,Does content avoid flashing more than 3 times/sec?,,
2.4.1,A,Operable,Bypass Blocks,"Is there a way to skip repetitive navigation (e.g., skip link)?",,
2.4.2,A,Operable,Page Titled,Does every page have a descriptive title?,,
2.4.3,A,Operable,Focus Order,Is focus order logical and predictable?,,
2.4.4,A,Operable,Link Purpose (In Context),Is link text descriptive of its destination?,,
2.4.5,AA,Operable,Multiple Ways,"Is there more than one way to find a page (search, nav, sitemap)?",,
2.4.6,AA,Operable,Headings & Labels,Are headings/labels clear and descriptive?,,
2.4.7,AA,Operable,Focus Visible,Is the keyboard focus indicator clearly visible?,,
2.5.1,A,Operable,Pointer Gestures,"Are complex gestures (e.g., swipe, pinch) avoidable or alternatives provided?",,
2.5.2,A,Operable,Pointer Cancellation,Can users cancel/dismiss input before activation?,,
2.5.3,A,Operable,Label in Name,Do labels match visible text for voice input users?,,
2.5.4,A,Operable,Motion Actuation,"Can motion-based inputs (e.g., shake, tilt) be disabled?",,
3.1.1,A,Understandable,Language of Page,"Is the page language defined (e.g., <html lang='en'>)?",,
3.1.2,AA,Understandable,Language of Parts,"Are language changes in content marked (e.g., foreign words)?",,
3.2.1,A,Understandable,On Focus,Does focusing on elements not trigger unexpected changes?,,
3.2.2,A,Understandable,On Input,Does entering data not cause unexpected navigation/updates?,,
3.2.3,AA,Understandable,Consistent Navigation,Is navigation consistent across pages?,,
3.2.4,AA,Understandable,Consistent Identification,Are elements with the same function consistently identified?,,
3.3.1,A,Understandable,Error Identification,Are input errors clearly indicated?,,
3.3.2,A,Understandable,Labels or Instructions,Are form fields properly labeled with instructions if needed?,,
3.3.3,AA,Understandable,Error Suggestion,Are suggestions provided for fixing input errors?,,
3.3.4,AA,Understandable,"Error Prevention (Legal, Financial, Data)","Can users review, correct, or confirm before submitting critical info?",,
4.1.1,A,Robust,Parsing,Is HTML code valid and free of parsing errors?,,
4.1.2,A,Robust,"Name, Role, Value","Do all UI components expose proper ARIA roles, states, and values?",,
4.1.3,AA,Robust,Status Messages,Are status messages programmatically conveyed to assistive tech?,,
